HEADWORD: Jet deau
<hw>Jet` d'eau"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Jets
d'eau</plw> <pr>(#)</pr></plu>. <ety>[F., a throw of water. See
<er>Jet</er> a shooting forth.]</ety> <def>A stream of water spouting,
esp. upward, from a fountain or pipe for ornament; also, the fountain or
pipe from which it issues.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

